<font color="#FF0000">TO DR. SPATA</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 28  2:25:34 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
The protestors were not right in breaking the law and destroying property. If they were, then all the rioters since then are fully justified to destroy property and inflict harm on others simply because there was an injustice performed by a government official.<br><br>
Dr. Spata, if you honestly believe you were right in your protesting, that is fine but don't pull the sacntimonious crap that you say you were trying to educate us.<br><br>
As a soldier we are trained to fight and possibly die for a greater good. Yes, some went beyond what was legal. Yes, weapons of destruction are indiscriminate. However you and thousands of other &quot;protestors&quot; actively sought out and attacked those of us who wore that uniform. You did not by any account educate anyone through your actions. You instead divided a nation and caused a deeper wound to fester.<br><br>
Had your protests been directed to the powers that sent us to Vietnam, I may have joined your cause. What happened to me was not an isolated incident. It has happened time and time again to me and others. Low paying jobs, Inadequate housing, and the comments all to often surface today.<br><br>
You sir have to have a reality check and stop trying to convince the world that what you did to us was right and just.
<p><code>-- ahernand@manc.edu  (Alex J Hernandez) </code><p>


